\title{dcce: Dynamic Common Correlated Effects Estimation for Panel Data}
\description{
Estimates heterogeneous coefficient models for large panels with cross-sectional dependence. Implements the Mean Group (MG), Common Correlated Effects (CCE), and Dynamic CCE (DCCE) estimators of Pesaran (2006) and Chudik and Pesaran (2015), the regularized CCE of Juodis (2022), and long-run estimators including CS-DL, CS-ARDL, and Pooled Mean Group (PMG) (Chudik et al. 2016; Shin et al. 1999) with full short-run / adjustment / long-run decomposition and delta-method inference. Provides a comprehensive cross-sectional dependence test suite (Pesaran 2015 CD, Juodis and Reese 2022 CDw, Baltagi et al. 2012 bias-adjusted CDw+, Fan et al. 2015 PEA, Pesaran and Xie 2021 CD*), the Pesaran (2007) CIPS panel unit root test, the Swamy (1970) and Pesaran and Yamagata (2008) slope homogeneity tests, a Hausman-type test for MG versus pooled, the exponent of cross-sectional dependence from Bailey et al. (2016, 2019), information criteria for CSA selection (Margaritella and Westerlund 2023), the rank condition classifier (De Vos et al. 2024), cross-section and wild bootstrap inference, and broom-compatible methods.
}
